It’s the time of year to recap the media highlights for the sponsors, so they can see their ‘return of investment’; all part of the business of being a professional rider. To compile these books, collect the data is a lot of work, to generate all the media exposure (on all sorts of media platforms) is a endless different task. Not sure how many riders go through the hassle, for me it’s part of the job, even though I’d rather ride my bike.

This man received a bicycle from @wheels4lifecharity last week, thanks to a fundraiser from @brausewettercarl who climbed Kilimanjaro earlier this year on a bike. This man uses the bike to transport the charcoal he made to a market 10 kilometres from his village. He will earn $1.50 per bag. He now has the opportunity to make some income to provide for his family in Tanzania. 
#GiveABikeChangeALife 
Looking for a meaningful Christmas gift? Gift somebody a gift certificate from our charity for Xmas. More info on our website:

NEW EDIT ALERT!!!
‘Once Upon A Time In Umbria’ 
24 years ago I thought I would slowly retire, so I bought a cool place in Umbria, Italy. Well, in the end I didn’t live this particular dream ( nor did I retire); but somebody else did. Last year I went down memory lane when I visited with my @shimanomtb #EP8 equipped EBike. 
A film by @creatur_productions & No Way Productions. Make sure to watch the full edit, link above.

Stoked on the new ‘Once Upon A Ride In Umbria’ film (Link in bio or go to the Shimano YouTube channel). 
So cool to visit my old farmhouse and the area I used to live on; but also great to stay at my sister Silvia’ incredible country house/hotel @villareyumbria and ride one of my favourite tours on the ancient Monte Cetona. Love that culture, landscape and people - e-bikes are the perfect way to explore. @shimanomtb

You can’t really call it a trail nor can I recommend to try it, unless ….
Well, someone had to do it. This is the latest episode of Trails & Tours around Switzerlands Disentis-Sedrun region; Laj Alv Descent is a steep and rocky hiking trail that turns into a field of rocks (which serve as the base of the ski slope in the winter). Fair to say there wasn’t much flow 😂, very trialsy and often momentum was your best friend. Watch the whole attempt on my YT Channel, link in bio, enjoy the breathtaking panoramic views. Not to mention getting up there first, but that’s a different story.  @rheinquelleregion @asd_experience

This was by far the biggest appearance of my career. Going ‘viral’ in 1987 in front of 41 million viewers on live TV. Wetten dass…? was a super popular TV game show where celebrity contestants like @janefonda would bet that I could ride my bike around a square of balance beams. Back then nobody could imagine how I would get around the corners. I won my bet and 3 weeks later I left Germany for my first ever trip to America…

Would you rather have a Reel go viral and be forgotten a few days (or minutes) later, or have a print magazine cover that people still remember,collect and treasure 30 yrs later. At the time it was sold in every shop or news stand. 
Personally I see the benefits in both mediums, both are great tools to communicate w our community and beyond. But I’am still more proud of my 450+ career cover shots than any social posts.

In 78 or 79 I met Franz Beckenbauer one block from where I lived in Emmendingen and received this Vita Malz autograph card, he and the legendary Sepp Maier did a appearance at the grand opening at the hair salon of the then @fcbayern coach’ Lóránt’ wife. You can never make a first impression twice. Thanks for taking the time, I will never forget, nor do I forget the rumours about your life time @adidas contract. Still wondering. Thank you Franz, RIP
